cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI 

The paper deals with optimizing resource allocation in Wi-Fi networks using deep reinforcement learning, which involves both networking and machine learning concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with information theory concepts such as channel assignment and throughput performance, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The use of machine learning algorithms for optimization also makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. The paper also deals with system-level optimization of Wi-Fi networks, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the use of reinforcement learning for decision-making makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category.
